Pad Thai
  --Joshua (didn't catch last name)

Sauce:
2 tbsp shoyu
1 tbsp fish sauce
3 tbsp sugar (palm, brown, or white)
2-3 tbsp tamarind paste

Add all the ingredients to a saucepan and cook on medium heat for ~5 min until it bubbles. Set aside.

Noodles:
5 shrimp, peeled and deveined
4-6 oz (100-150g) rice noodles (pad thai noodles)
1 c bean sprouts
1/4 c chinese chives chopped into 1" lengths, reserve a few for garnish (can sub spring onions)
1 egg
1 medium carrot, sliced or shredded
1 clove garlic, peeled and chopped
1 small shallot, peeled and chopped
1-2 tbsp oil (coconut, canola, or olive)
1/4 package firm tofu, cubed
1/4 c roasted peanuts, crushed
1 tbsp chili powder for garnish
1-2 lime wedge for garnish

Heat 5 c water and pour over noodles in a heat proof bowl/pot. Let them cook for 7-8 min and then drain and cool with cold water. Put back in vessel and cover with cold water. Heat oil in pan over high heat and fry tofu until it changes color a bit to golden brown outside, ~4 min; remove and set aside. Add shrimp and cook for 1-2 min; remove and set aside. Turn the heat to medium, add oil, and when hot, add garlic and shallots and fry until fragrant, 1 min, then add carrot and fry for another 3 s. Move to one side and quickly cook the egg by scrambling it for ~30 s. Add noodles and sauce and stir until well coated. Add in the tofu and shrimp, toss. Add bean sprouts and chives, turn off heat and mix everything together. Serve on a plate garnished with peanuts, chili powder, chives, and lime wedge(s).


Notes: if you can't find tamarind paste, can make a substitute:
1 tbsp worchestershire sauce
1 tbsp ketchup
1 tbsp lime juice
1 tbsp rice vinegar
